The paper deals with wireless network operations and data aggregation, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of distributed machine learning and intelligent mobile applications, which fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel scheme for interference management, which is relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
